resources.string: This is a list of international cricket grounds in India that have hosted at least one international cricket match (Test, ODI or T20I). International cricket was held in India for the first time in December 1933 when the Gymkhana Ground in Bombay played host to the India-England Test match. The first ODI match in India was held at the Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel Stadium, Ahmedabad in 1981.
